results.name: Triangular array of natural numbers (greater than 1) arranged by ordered prime signature.
comment: The main diagonals are sequences A000040 (the prime numbers) and A055932 (the Quet prime signatures). A096011 displays other prime signatures which are not in A025487 (the least prime signature sequence).
example: a(28) = 18 because 18 = 2*3*3, thus has ordered prime signature (1,2).
results.author: _Alford Arnold_, Jul 24 2004
